content.description: Pull-on with a left-hand crimp and a right-hand two-finger pocket. Make a big move out left to a two-finger pocket and squeeze your right heel onto the shelf near your right hand. Catch another two-finger pocket with the right-hand. Throw out left to a small pinch and bump it to a crimp. Place a high right toe and fire for the jug at the lip. Most likely easier for shorter folks.
content.location: From the parking, cross the road and follow the ravine for a short distance. Turn right and walk straight up the hill. Boulder is a small roof about halfway up the hill. The approach shouldn't take you more than 5 min.

pathTokens: Land of High Bouldering AKA The Ridge

content.description: A small roof which hosts a single line.
